Reproducibility & Usage
1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/USERNAME/REPOSITORY.git
cd REPOSITORY
2. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt
3. Add the dataset

Place the 12 Beijing air-quality CSV files inside:

AirQuality/

The notebook expects the filenames listed in AirQuality/README.md.

4. Run the notebook

Open and run:

FLTA2026-Task-Free-Federated-Continual-Forecasting.ipynb

The notebook is organized in the same order as the experiment:

Imports and configuration
Data preprocessing
Model and replay-buffer definitions
Federated base training
Drift-threshold calibration
Continual-learning methods
Full grid execution
Table and result export
